cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.GR, cs.IT, cs.LG

This paper deals with image fusion, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves the use of pre-estimations and a bilateral solver, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR). The paper also discusses the use of confidence maps, which is a concept related to information theory (cs.IT) and the evaluation of the proposed method involves objective and subjective metrics, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG).
